#stance=stance2
#originalStanceText=No
#originalTopic=should-the-us-have-universal-healthcare
What is moral about forcing every single citizen into a single-payer system? What is moral about taking someone's hard-earned   money   and giving it to someone who didn't earn it. The points made in this article sound very nice on the surface. But there is no workable plan to accomplish them. It is one thing to say "everybody has a right to   health care  ", it is another thing to be able to accomplish it. The health care system in this country can be fixed very easily. How about lowering   taxes   on medical providers? Nobody has a right to live off other people's labor. 